Maven Java Web Application: CI/CD Pipeline to Tomcat 10.1

Overview
Java web application built with Maven. Originally created in 2022 and modernized in 2026. Automated CI/CD pipeline from GitHub to Apache Tomcat 10.1 on AWS EC2.

Tech Stack
Language: Java JDK 21 LTS
Build Tool: Apache Maven 3.9.6
CI/CD: Jenkins
Code Quality: SonarQube 2026.1 LTA
Application Server: Apache Tomcat 10.1

Pipeline Workflow
1. Commit: Code pushed to GitHub triggers Jenkins via webhook
2. Build: mvn clean verify runs JUnit 5 tests and packages .war
3. Analysis: SonarQube performs static analysis and quality gate check
4. Deploy: WAR uploaded to Tomcat Manager API using curl

Prerequisites
JDK 21
Maven 3.9.6
Tomcat 10.1 running on EC2

Build Locally
git clone https://github.com/JimmyT96/java-cicd-jenkins-sonar
cd java-cicd-jenkins-sonar
mvn clean verify

Artifact: target/maven-web-app.war

Deploy to Tomcat
curl -u admin:password -T target/maven-web-app.war "http://18.182.36.207:8080/manager/text/deploy?path=/maven-web-app&update=true"

Access: http://18.182.36.207:8080/maven-web-app

Key Notes
Uses Jakarta EE http://jakarta.servlet for Tomcat 10.1 compatibility
Deploys via Tomcat Manager API
Context path: /maven-web-app

